<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="13May1924"><font color="red">13 May 1924</font> <i>BLHW</i> (to Harriet Weaver): I am afraid I have not shown very much interest in [the second French edition of <i>Ulysses</i>] or anything else lately except in puzzling over Shem and Shaun in my haunted dungeon &hellip; Punkt &hellip; I am very fatigued, in sight of the operating table and half stupified by the gloom, noise, expense and uncertainty in which I try to work &hellip; I shall try to finish the first half of Shaun before the next big event &mdash; whatever it may be. </div>
